# perpprompt-reader configuration template.
#
# Copy to /opt/perpbot/config/reader_env and edit. config/ is gitignored, so the
# real LAN IP never enters the repo:
#
#   sudo -u perpbot cp /opt/perpbot/dashboard/reader_env.example \
#       /opt/perpbot/config/reader_env
#
# Bind address. Pin to perpBOT's LAN interface so a no-auth service never answers
# on any other interface. Leave unset to use the code default (0.0.0.0), which is
# still LAN-only on this host. Uncomment and set to the real LAN IP:
#
# PERPBOT_READER_HOST=192.168.1.10

# Optional overrides (code defaults shown):
# PERPBOT_READER_PORT=8090
# PERPBOT_CHROMADB_PATH=/opt/perpbot/chromadb
